===Etymology 1===
The definitions related to “to examine” come from the “kernel” sense, i.e. “to go to the core” ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Generally thought to be of {{der|zh|sit}} origin. It has been compared to {{cog|bo|རག་ཙེ}}, {{cog|mjw|rak}} ({{zh-ref|Gong, 2002}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). However, {{zh-ref|Hill (2012)}} rejects the connection to the {{cog|bo|-}} word because most words ending with {{m|bo||ཙེ}} are loanwords from Chinese words ending with the {{zh-l|*子}} suffix.

{{zh-ref|Smith (2011)}} groups this word with the following terms into a word family meaning “root, germ, generative core”:
* {{och-l|荄|id=1|grassroot}} and its derivative {{och-l|根|root}},
* {{och-l|骸|(human) bones}} (also noted by {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}),
* {{och-l|孩|child}},
* {{och-l|亥|sprouting stage}}, i.e. "the moon’s first appearance" > "twelfth earthly branch".

